 combination\nof in-situ star formation, more than a dozen low-mass mergers, and $1.4\\pm1.2$\nearly ($z=3.1\\pm1.3$) major merger. The rapid assembly period ended early,\nlimiting the fraction of accreted stars. We conclude by providing detailed\nquantitative predictions for the assembly history of the MW.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 May 2020 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Mar 2021 14:21:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-31"}
